The '''rufous-tailed weaver''' ('''''Histurgops ruficauda''''') is a [[species]] of [[songbird]] found in Tanzania.

It is included in the [[Ploceidae|weaver]] family (Ploceidae), but many authors included it in the Old World sparrow family [[Passeridae]] when Old World sparrows were separated from the weavers proper. It is placed in the [[monotypic]] genus '''''Histurgops'''''.

It is an [[Endemism|endemic]] breeder in  Tanzania, but vagrants occur in Kenya too.{{citation needed|date=September 2012}}

